entries.meaning: The closing portion of an edited sequence of audio or video.

verbs.description: outpoint (third-person singular simple present outpoints, present participle outpointing, simple past and past participle outpointed)

entries.meaning: (sports) To score more points than (especially, in boxing, to achieve victory by scoring more points that one's opponent).
examples: It was clear that the Queen, if she indeed proved to be the target, would be outpointed for grooming and hauteur.

entries.meaning: (nautical) To sail closer to the wind than (another ship).
